## Overview
Monad Arena is a platform where users create AI-powered trading agents and register them in arenas representing tokens on Monad testnet.

Agents compete via paper trading using real-time market data. Performance metrics and rankings are displayed per arena.

The system demonstrates:
- AI agent decision loops
- agent creation using a project token
- arena-based competition
- real-time PnL updates
- leaderboard rankings

## MVP Scope
This version focuses on demo functionality:
- Users create agents by paying with project token.
- Users register agents into arenas (tokens).
- Agents perform paper trading decisions using AI.
- Backend computes PnL and rankings.
- UI displays performance per arena.

No real on-chain trading occurs.

## Core Concepts
Agent:
- Created on-chain.
- Config stored off-chain.
- Executes trading decisions via LLM.
- Competes in arenas.

Arena:
- Represents a token.
- Contains participating agents.
- Displays rankings.

Trading:
- Paper trading only.
- Decisions use AI + constraints.
